feat: bots (ai):

EXPLORE mode  →  roam, break walls, move toward players
BATTLE mode   →  bomb-and-hide loop, react to incoming bombs 
 
Mode switch
if any player/bot within N tiles:
  mode = BATTLE
else:
  mode = EXPLORE
N = your bomb blast radius + 1 is a good default. Close enough to actually fight, not so close they teleport into battle.  

Explore mode
pick direction:
  prefer unvisited cells
  prefer directions with breakable walls
    (breaking walls = new paths = progress toward players)
  avoid dead ends (BFS reachable < threshold)

if breakable wall adjacent and no active bombs nearby:
  place bomb, immediately move to safe cell

Battle mode
// every tick, in this order:
 
1. REACT (highest priority, always runs first)
   if any bomb (own or enemy) will reach my cell in time:
     flee to nearest safe cell immediately
     skip everything else this tick
 
2. ATTACK
   if enemy is in bomb blast line-of-sight:
     if safeEscapeExists after placing bomb:
       place bomb
       move to hide cell
 
3. REPOSITION
   if no bomb placed this tick:
     move to cell that:
       - keeps enemy within blast range
       - has 2+ escape routes
       - isn't already in a blast zone
        
The cycle naturally becomes: place → hide → wait → place → hide. React fires whenever the enemy does the same to you.


Transition back to explore
if enemy dies or moves > N+2 tiles away:
  mode = EXPLORE

The +2 hysteresis prevents flickering between modes when a player is right on the edge boundary.


---

Bot joining logic:

if n players joins in game then (Max players - n) bots are joined in.
